														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1382028">
									

<p>It does, doesn't it?</p>
<p>ahninjas: Here's my explanation on the &quot;anything is discussable&quot; phenomonon, copied from the Meta-Thread.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Officially,&nbsp;it&nbsp;should&nbsp;be&nbsp;pronounced&nbsp;'es-see-pee-ception',&nbsp;but&nbsp;'skipception'&nbsp;IS&nbsp;easier&nbsp;to&nbsp;say.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Wait,&nbsp;Class&nbsp;As&nbsp;are&nbsp;short-term&nbsp;memory,&nbsp;not&nbsp;Class&nbsp;B...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>It's a glitch in the Wikidot Matrix. Every page on a wiki must have a discussion page. Even discussion pages. Hence the metathread: a discussion page for every discussion page and forum thread on the site, including itself. The graph of discussion pages has three levels and no loose nodes, with a single arrow pointing from a regular page to its discussion page, every discussion page and forum thread point to the metathread, and the metathread points to itself.</p>
<p>Now go take a Class B before your brain implodes.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
